From: Michal Kubecek <mkubecek@suse.cz>
Date: Wed, 2 Nov 2022 17:20:03 +0100
Subject: net: disable CONFIG_NET_DMA code
Patch-mainline: Never, code removed in mainline 3.18-rc1
References: CVE-2019-3837 bsc#1131430

As reported in CVE-2019-3837, IOAT DMA code in TCP Rx path suffers from
race conditions resulting in memory leaks which can be abused for denial of
service attacks.

The IOAT DMA code was marked broken by commit 77873803363c ("net_dma: mark
broken") in mainline 3.13-rc5 and later removed completely by commit
7bced397510a ("net_dma: simple removal") in mainline 3.18-rc1. The commit
messages also mention that in practice, the performance benefit was rather
poor so it seems more appropriate to drop the code in SLE11-SP4-LTSS as
well, keeping only parts needed to preserve kABI.

Signed-off-by: Michal Kubecek <mkubecek@suse.cz>
